|NPCID|69339| |LVL|Level 92| |ABIL|137884,136691,137990,138003| |NDIS|94222,94825,| |ST|While fighting (npc:69339) you may have to use the near by Lightning Rod, so unlike many other elites you will have to remain near his spawn.<br/><br/>(npc:69339)'s main attack, (spell:137884), needs to be interrupted when ever possible.<br/>Each time (npc:69339) successfully casts (spell:137884), anyone hit by it will gain a stack of Electrified causing 10000 nature damage per second.<br/><br/>If any of your group get too many stacks of this debuff to be healable, they will have to remove it by using the Lightning Rod. While this removes the debuff, it also causes a (npc:69354) to spawn and attack you.<br/>Each (npc:69354) melee's for around 20000 nature damage, and each additional (npc:69354) that spawns increases the damage of all other elementals by 20%.<br/><br/>Found in (map:928) (44.50, 61.00, 928, "(npc:69339)")|
|NPCID|69341| |LVL|Level 92| |ABIL|136872,136716,136736,137334| |NDIS|94222,94708| |ST|During your fight with (npc:69341), he will call (spell:136734) to run around underneath him. <br/>If any of these spirits run through you, they deal 25,000 nature damage and pacify you for 5 seconds, leaving you unable to attack or cast spells.<br/><br/>During this stampede Kros will cast (spell:136716), fearing everyone in combat for 3 seconds. Therefore it is ideal to have a ranged dps, or a great dino-dodging melee to interrupt the fear.<br/><br/>Every 50 seconds throughout the fight, a (npc:69227) will appear next to the Ritual Stone. At this point (npc:69341) will break off his attacks and attempt to eat the Saurok with (spell:136872), restoring 20% of his health unless you kill the Saurok before he reaches it. Once you kill the Saurok you will have to deal with Kros' short enrage, which is dispellable.<br/><br/>You can tank Kros away from the altar to give you time to kill the Saurok.<br/><br/>Found in (map:928) (55.20, 87.70, 928, "(npc:69341)")|
|NPCID|69347| |LVL|Level 92| |ABIL|136854,136898,137256,137074,136847| |NDIS|94823,94222| |ST|This is the top half of a Drakkari Colossus that remains stationary on the nearby altar.<br/>Once engaged the (npc:69347) continually tries to attack a target in melee. If at any time there are no available targets in range, it will begin casting (spell:136854) at it's current highest threat, causing massive damage.<br/><br/>As long as there is at least one player in melee range, it will continue it's basic melee attacks in combination with it's other 3 main abilities.<br/><br/>Ranged can stand to the sides of the altar to avoid all his attacks.<br/><br/>Found in (map:928) (49.90, 20.70, 928, "(npc:69347)")|
|NPCID|69396| |LVL|Level 92| |ABIL|138660,139961,138661,136866,136865| |NDIS|94706,94222| |ST|The most significant ability is (spell:136866). This is a conal aoe both in front of and behind Cera hitting for arond 100k per second to anyone caught in it.<br/><br/>During the fight Cera will also pick a random party member to (spell:138660) at, dealing moderate damage to her target and anyone near by if she lands on them, though with a 3 second cast this is rather easy to avoid.<br/><br/>Her only unique ability is the use of (spell:136865), which despite the name deflects all incoming damage from the front for 5 seconds, rather then reflecting it.<br/><br/>Found in (map:928) (57.90, 79.20, 928, "(npc:69396)")|
|NPCID|69471| |LVL|Level 92| |ABIL|137140,137402| |NDIS|94707,94222| |ST|Warlord Teng's main attack is a frontal aoe every 20 seconds (spell:137140), which hits for around 200000 shadow damage. <br/>This attack has a three second cast making it easy to avoid, however it leaves behind a large aoe for 1 minute which also does significant shadow damage.<br/><br/>Every 20 seconds Teng will activate a Mogu Sarcophagus around the walls of the room. This will cause a (npc:69466) to spawn and target you with (spell:137125) for 5 seconds. If this channel completes you will be sucked into the Mogu Sarcophagus and take 180000 nature damage over 10 seconds (spell:137280). The channel can be broken by line of sight, causing a small spirit wrath aoe to spawn.<br/><br/>Found in (map:928) (35.70, 63.80, 928, "(npc:69471)")|
