|NPCID|67572| |NAME|Dungeon Master Vishas| |LVL|Rank 1.4| |ABIL|133286,133288| |ST|(npc:67572) has two abilities.<br/><br/>(spell:133288) deals Shadow Damage and leaves a debuff, increasing the Shadow damage you take by 150%. <br/>(spell:133286) deals additional Fire damage with (npc:67572)'s melee attacks. A couple of these buffed melee attacks can kill you.<br/><br/>Your main priority is to avoid (npc:67572) melee attacks while he's buffed with (spell:133286).<br/><br/><b>Interrupt (spell:133286).<br/><b>Use fear, root, incapacitate, or snare to get away from (npc:68257).|	
|NPCID|68255| |NAME|Dippy| |LVL|Rank 2.1| |ABIL|134537| |ST|(npc:68255) uses (spell:134537) which deals a huge amount of damage and can kill you with one hit. It has a 1 second cast time and only hits you if you are in melee range when the cast finishes. (npc:68255) has a powerful melee attack.<br/><br/><b>Whenever (npc:68255) takes damage, he gets knocked back.<br/><b>Don't back him into a wall or he can't be knocked down.<br/><b>Use spells and abilities with a short cast time.<br/><b>You want him taking damage as often as possible to stop him getting close.<br/><br/>It's not as simple for melee classes. Try and stun (npc:68255) frequently and deal as much damage as you can (in melee range). Use ranged abilities, even if inefficient. Use all your offensive cooldowns as soon as the fight begins. You will need to use all your offensive cooldowns to beat the 2-minute enrage timer.|	
|NPCID|67269| |NAME|Kirrawk| |LVL|Rank 2.2| |ABIL|97474,132673,135234,132670| |ST|(npc:67269) has two abilities<br/><br/>(spell:97474) which (npc:67269) uses the most.<br/>(spell:135234) forms above (npc:67269) and keeps dealing damge, but it can be interrupted.<br/><br/>Your main priority is avoiding (spell:132668). These twisters appear about every 20 seconds and will start chasing you. If hit, you will be thrown in the air and dealt a lot of damage from (npc:67269). If (npc:67269) is hit, he will be thrown in the air giving you a free moment.<br/><br/><b>When a twister spawns, position yourself so that (npc:67269) is in the tornado's path as it comes towards you.<br/><br/><b>For ranged DPS, stay in melee range of (npc:67269), to make positioning easier.<br/><br/><b>Interrupt (spell:135234) as much as you can.<br/><br/><b>Don't interrupt (spell:97474), unless you have good defense against melee attacks.|	
|NPCID|67525| |NAME|Fran| |LVL|Rank 2.3| |ABIL|133227,133213| |ST|(npc:67525) and (npc:67524) are separate opponents, but because (npc:67524) has (npc:67525) riding on his back, it's like killing one opponent.<br/><br/>They use the following abilities.<br/><br/>(spell:133213) is used by (npc:67525), which explodes when it hits the ground, dealing Fire damage.<br/>(spell:133308) is used by (npc:67524), which traps you for 5 seconds.<br/>(spell:133227) is used by (npc:67525), where he surrounds you with explosives that detonate after 3 seconds.<br/><br/>(npc:67524) will trap you with (spell:133308) and then (npc:67525) will use (spell:133227) while you're trapped. (npc:67524)'s trap will always expire before (npc:67525)'s explosives detonate. Quickly move away from the explosives as soon as the trap disappears.<br/><br/>It's best that (npc:67524) and (npc:67525) are killed at the same time, as the fight is easier when they are both alive.<br/><br/>If (npc:67524) dies first, then (npc:67525) will use (spell:133213) way more often.<br/><br/>If (npc:67525) dies first, then (npc:67524) will become frenzied. (spell:133296) will deal 250% increased damage.|	
