|NPCID|68254| |NAME|King Kulaka| |LVL|Rank 2.4| |ABIL|44531| |ST|(npc:68254) uses (spell:44531) which increases his running speed.<br/><br/>(npc:68254) hits hard and will only melee you.<br/><br/>Melee players can't do much except stand there trying to kill him, before he kills them. They need to use their defensive cooldowns wisely.<br/><br/>Ranged players need to keep (npc:68254) at a distance, as his attacks are very damaging. He can be rooted, slowed or stunned, etc.|	
|NPCID|67594| |NAME|Blat| |LVL|Rank 3.1| |ABIL|133302| |ST|(npc:67594) uses (spell:133302), which creates new copies of himself. These replicas move slowly so aren't much of a problem, so long as the fight doesn't last too long.<br/><br/>(npc:67594) only uses a melee attack on you with about 6k damage, the replicas also deal the same damage.<br/><br/>To end the fight, just kill (npc:67594), the replicas don't need to die.<br/><br/><b>Ranged players just need to keep (npc:67594) away, by rooting or slowing him.<br/><br/><b>Melee players need to backpedal during the fight, to help reduce the damage from (npc:67594) and its replicas.|	
|NPCID|67268| |NAME|Sanoriak| |LVL|Rank 3.2| |ABIL|136333,15536,132666,135237,135236,136334,33975| |ST|(npc:67268) has five abilities.<br/><br/>(spell:132666) creates a wall of fire around you, that keeps getting smaller. There is always a hole for your to get out. Deals a lot of damage and one hit can almost kill you.<br/>(spell:135237) gives a debuff, making you take increased fire damage. While debuffed, (npc:67268) will try to hit you hard with (spell:135236).<br/>(spell:15536) and (spell:33975) both deal fire damage and are often used by (npc:67268).<br/><br/>Your two main priorities are (spell:132666) and (spell:135237).<br/><br/>All of (npc:67268)'s abilities can be interrupted. It is best to save your interrupting spells for (spell:135237).<br/><br/>With some practice (spell:132666) is easily dealt with, so you shouldn't need to interrupt it.<br/><br/><b>When (spell:132666) starts, just stand still and look for the opening, then get out.<br/><br/><b>(spell:135237) should be interrupted.<br/><br/><b>You can also use specific class abilities to stop debuffs or to remove them.<br/><br/><b>If debuffed by (spell:135237), stay away from (npc:67268) until it runs out.<br/><br/><b>The damage from (spell:15536) and (spell:33975) should be manageable.|	
|NPCID|68253| |NAME|Ixx| |LVL|Rank 3.3| |ABIL|134777| |ST|(npc:68253) uses (spell:134777), which targets a semi-circle area in front of him. This will kill you with one hit.<br/><br/>(npc:68253) has a powerful melee attack dealing about 40k damage.<br/><br/>Your main priority is avoiding (spell:134777), with it's devasting damage and short cast time of 1.5 seconds.<br/><br/><b>Melee players and casters who can cast while moving, should keep running around close to (npc:68253), while attacking him.<br/><br/><b>Casters can also stand right under (npc:68253) (middle of his hitbox). Then just run through him when he starts casting (spell:134777).<br/><br/><b>(npc:68253) spawns with only a fraction of his life, so make good use of your execute abilities.|	
|NPCID|68251| |NAME|Mazhareen| |LVL|Rank 3.4| |ABIL|| |ST|(npc:68251) will only melee you. Her damage increases as her health lowers, making the end of the fight the hardest part.<br/><br/><b>Keep all your cooldowns for when (npc:68251)'s health drops below 50%.<br/><br/><b>Melee players can't do much except stand there trying to kill her, before she kills them. They need to save their defensive cooldowns and stuns for the end of the fight.<br/><br/><b>Ranged players, can root, slow, or stun (npc:68251) to keep away from her.|	
|NPCID|67540| |NAME|Crush| |LVL|Rank 4.1| |ABIL|133254| |ST|(npc:67540) uses (spell:133254), where he charges towards you, in a straight line.<br/><br/>It is easy to avoid (spell:133254), by stepping to the side when (npc:67540) starts charging. (npc:67540) will be stunned for a few seconds by running into a wall. If he does hit you, you will both be stunned and you will take a lot of damage.<br/><br/>It is easy to recover from his charge, it's more of problem that you lose several seconds of uptime on (npc:67540). Too much downtime might result in the 2-minute enrage timer.|	
|NPCID|68377| |NAME|Leona Earthwind| |LVL|Rank 4.2| |ABIL|134743,129888,134741| |ST|(npc:68377) has three abilities.<br/><br/>(spell:134741) deals 50k - 60k damage.<br/>(spell:129888) will silence you for a few seconds so you can't cast spells.<br/>(spell:134743) summons 3 (npc:68383), which will chase you and deal decent damage per hit.<br/><br/>The hardest part of this fight is managing the (npc:68383). Some classes are going to find this fight a lot easier than others.<br/><br/>Some classes can spread the damage they do to Leona onto the (npc:68383). For these classes, the fight will be much easier. If you aren't an AoE class you might have difficulties. Try to burn the (npc:68383) down as fast as possible, or, if you trust your single target DPS, just stun/cc/ignore them and burn down (npc:68377)<br/><br/><b>Interrupt (spell:134741) as often as you can.<br/><b>Whenever (spell:129888) is cast at your location, move away from it.<br/><b>Most melee classes can safely ignore the (spell:129888).|	
|NPCID|67485| |NAME|Dominika the Illusionist| |LVL|Rank 4.3| |ABIL|133123,133129| |ST|(npc:67485) has two abilities<br/><br/>(spell:133123) which can be interrupted.<br/>(spell:133129) summons a copy of (npc:67485) each time she is hit. These adds spawn randomly around the arena and have very little health (only 1 HP) and will also use (spell:133123) on you.<br/><br/>Some melee classes will find this fight difficult with new adds spawning with every melee attack.<br/><br/>Many classes will have the ability to simply take down (npc:67485)<br/><br/>Other classes will need to clear the adds. An easier way to kill off adds is to interrupt (npc:67485) when the fight begins. She will then melee you, so you can move her into a corner. This will make the adds spawn in an arc around you, letting you AoE them more easily.<br/><br/>The adds have very little health so AoE them down before they overwhelm you.<br/><br/>You control the adds spawning so find a balance between enough DPS and enough add handling.|	
|NPCID|67451| |NAME|Deeken| |LVL|Rank 4.4| |ABIL|133169| |ST|(npc:67451) uses (spell:133169) which knocks you back and deals damage.<br/><br/>There are moving electric currents on the floor of the arena, that will deal about 80k damage if stepped on. You can jump over them.<br/><br/>Your main priority is to avoid the electric fields, as they will give you the most damage.<br/><br/>Save a defensive cooldown in case (npc:67451) knocks you into an electric field with (spell:133169).<br/><br/>It's a straightforward fight once you figure out how to dodge the electric fields.|	
|NPCID|70677| |NAME|Master Boom Boom| |LVL|Rank 4 Special| |ABIL|140890,140912,140892,140893,140894| |ST|(npc:70677) is a Rank 4 special boss that requires a quest to unlock.<br/><br/>The item which allows you to receive the quest and purchase the card to challenge the boss is (item:97980). The easiest way to farm this item it to take control of (npc:60754) during (qid:30821) and keep killing Hozen without turning in the quest until you get it. The item will appear in your inventory.<br/><br/>Fight begins with (npc:70677) casting (spell:140891) at you which you must dodge to avoid roughly 50k damage and stun for 2 seconds. Any explosives that were successfully dodged will arm themselves on the ground and remain there for you to avoid throughout the fight.<br/><br/>Roughly 10 to 15 seconds into the fight (or sooner if his HP reaches 50%) (npc:70677) will jump to the center and arm a stack of dynamite called (spell:140924), in which 4 fuses will spawn randomly along the outer walls and quickly make its way towards to middle to detonate.<br/><br/>You must VERY quickly walk on top of each fuse to stomp it out (look for a small red circle around the end of the fuse) while also dodging any explosives armed on the ground to avoid being stunned. Tthe fuses spawn locations are random, sometimes all 4 will appear next to each other making it easy, other times all 4 on opposite corners, making it most likely game over. Letting any fuse reach the middle will result in nearly 10 million in damage, instantly killing you.|	
|NPCID|70678| |NAME|Grandpa Grumplefoot| |LVL|Rank 4 Special| |ABIL|141020,140983,140950,140982,140988,140969| |ST|(npc:70678) is a Rank 4 special boss that requires a quest to unlock. The item (item:97978) is obtained by targeting (npc:70678) (65.0, 60.2, 809, "(npc:71082)") in (map:809) and typing /dance.<br/><br/>(npc:70678) begins the find by throwing (npc:70693) and (npc:70692) randomly in the arena. Don't touch the red (npc:70693) as they will explode on contact but you can touch the blue (npc:70692) if you're low on health and it will heal you for 50k. <br/><br/>At around 40% HP, (npc:70678) will take off his backpack and begins adding (npc:70735), these spawn very quickly and will kill you instantly. The (npc:70735) will also hop towards you every few seconds so keep moving and stay away from them. <br/><br/>Use all your cooldowns as soon as he removes his backpack to defeat him quickly and or else the (npc:70735) will soon surround you and kill you.|	
|NPCID|70666| |NAME|Ty'thar| |LVL|Rank 4 Special| |ABIL|140868,140862,140886| |ST|(npc:70666) is a Rank 4 special boss that requires a quest to unlock. The quest begins with (item:97990) which is dropped from level 90 Kor'Kron NPCs (60.0, 60.0, 11, "Kor'Krons") in (map:11).<br/><br/>You have to use the special abilities given to you durin the fight.<br/><br/><b>When he casts (spell:140862), move left.<br/><b>When he uses (spell:140868), move right.<br/><b>Move backwards when he casts (spell:140886).<br/><br/>Make sure you're in the correct position when his cast finishes.|	
|NPCID|67591| |NAME|Millie Watt| |LVL|Rank 5.1| |ABIL|133363,133362,133361,133306| |ST|(npc:67591) uses three abilities<br/><br/>(spell:133361) is used the most and deals about 7k damage per second.<br/>(spell:133363) creates a damaging electrical pool.<br/>(spell:133362) turns you into a chicken for 15 seconds. You can zap yourself out of this spell by taking damage from (spell:133363).<br/><br/>Your main priority is to manage (spell:133362). The best way to do this is:<br/><br/><b>Stand in an electrical pool for a moment, just before (npc:67591) finishes casting (spell:133362). The electrical damage will zap you back into character, ending (spell:133362) straight away.<br/><br/><b>Always move off the electrical pools when they appear (you only step on them to break (spell:133362)).<br/><br/>Staightforward fight once you manage to deal with (spell:133362).|	
|NPCID|67596| |NAME|Fjoll| |LVL|Rank 5.2| |ABIL|133344,133346,133349,79894,133332| |ST|(npc:67596) uses four abilities<br/><br/>(spell:133344) is used the most and can be interrupted.<br/><br/>(spell:133349) creates large  void zones on the ground, which are easy to avoid.<br/><br/>(spell:133332) deals about 65k damage and will knock you back. It can be dangerous if you are knocked back into a fiery void.<br/><br/>(spell:79894) may be used, if you take to long to kill (npc:67596).<br/><br/>(npc:67596) will summon small void zones that look like purple fire. They are very damaging and will kill you within about 3 seconds.<br/><br/><b>Your main priority is to avoid the fiery voids.<br/><b>Stand with your back by a wall, to prevent yourself from getting knocked into a fiery void.<br/><b>Move out of the (spell:133349) voids when they appear at your location.<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:133344)|	
|NPCID|68252| |NAME|Proboskus| |LVL|Rank 5.3| |ABIL|47008,124860,124935| |ST|(npc:68252) has two abilities<br/><br/>(spell:124935) is very damaging, but can be interrupted. You will be hit with 28% of your health as damage, every second for 6 seconds.<br/><br/>(spell:124860) is channelled for 10 seconds, where large rain drops fall around the arena. These drops can be deadly, dealing about 200k damage.<br/><br/>(npc:68252) deals about 50k damage, but he mainly casts spells, so won't melee attack too much.<br/><br/><b>Interrupt (spell:124935)<br/><b>To avoid (spell:124860), have your camera angled above you and zoom right out. This will help you see the water drops.<br/><br/>At 20% health (npc:68252) will enrage. His attacks become deadly for most classes. You need to incapacitate or stun him and finish him with ranged attacks.<br/><br/>Note that (npc:68252) won't enrage if (spell:124860) is being cast when he drops to 20% health. So you can get him to 21% or 22% health and wait for (spell:124860) to start. Then burn him down as hard as you can while (spell:124860) is channeling.|	
