|NPCID|70736| |NAME|Splat| |LVL|Rank 5 Special| |ABIL|141034| |ST|(npc:70736) is a Rank 5 special boss that you have to unlock. The quest begin with (item:97982) from (item:92813) which is awarded for doing scenarios.(npc:70736) is a stronger version of (npc:67594).<br/><br/>(npc:70736) has no ability and uses a melee attack on you. As the fight goes on, new copies of (npc:70736) keep appearing. Fortunately, they move very slowly, but if the fight drags on for too long, they might end up being a problem. To finish the fight, you only need to kill Blat, not the copies.<br/><br/>If you are a ranged DPS, all you need to do is keep Blat and its copies at a safe distance by slowing or rooting them and moving around. The copies of (npc:70736) should not be a problem, and even if they do manage to hit you a few times, you will easily survive.<br/><br/>If you are a melee DPS, you need to backpedal for the entire fight. This will cause you to take much less damage from (npc:70736) and its copies.|	
|NPCID|70648| |NAME|Doopy| |LVL|Rank 5 Special| |ABIL|142804,142753| |ST|(npc:70648) is a Rank 5 special boss that you have to unlock. The quest begin with (item:97984) obtained by defeating (npc:71438) (47.8, 14.6, 492, "(npc:70648)"), a level 25 battle pet located in (map:492).<br/><br/>(npc:70648) works the same way as (npc:68255) but he is bigger and slower. The key to this fight is to continue knocking back (npc:70648) while killing (npc:68255) first.|	
|NPCID|68256| |NAME|Yikkan Izu| |LVL|Rank 6.1| |ABIL|134795| |ST|(npc:68256) uses (spell:134795), which disorients you for 6 seconds. This can be interrupted.<br/><br/>(npc:68256) summons 4 ravens every 8 seconds. You need to kill them before the next pack spawns. If you kill more than 4 ravens at the same time, (npc:68256) will become enraged for a few seconds.<br/><br/>The more extra ravens you kill, the more enraged (npc:68256) will become.<br/><br/>Your main priority is to kill the ravens as soon as they appear.<br/><br/>Watch his buff (spell:134789), when it's gone or at 1-2 stacks, then use some light AoE spells (that don't hit more then 4 targets), when it stacks to 3-4, then single target (npc:68256). Those stacks will drop off after 2 seconds.<br/><br/>You should easily beat the enrage timer, even if you spend time killing the ravens.|	
|NPCID|67588| |NAME|Akama| |LVL|Rank 6.2| |ABIL|139963,39945,136194,126209,79797| |ST|(npc:67588) has four abilities<br/><br/>(spell:39945) deals about 100k damage and is cast frequently<br/>(spell:136194) summons wolves that will fight alongside (npc:67588) until killed.<br/>(spell:79797) deals about 40k damage and knocks you back.<br/>(spell:126209) applies a stacking buff on (npc:67588) making his melee attacks deal more damage.<br/><br/>Your main priority is to kill the wolves as fast as possible, as they deal decent damage.<br/><br/>(npc:67588) begins with a weak melee attack, but it grows stronger as the fight drags on.<br/><br/>Save defensive cooldowns for the end of the fight to manage (spell:126209).<br/><br/><b>(spell:39945) needs to be interrupted.|	
|NPCID|68305| |NAME|Smash Hoofstomp| |LVL|Rank 6.3| |ABIL|134623, 134650| |ST|(npc:68305) has two abilities<br/><br/>(spell:134623) deals 35k damage and knocks you back.<br/>(spell:134650) prevents (npc:68305) from being damaged from the front. The shield lasts for 10 seconds.<br/><br/>(npc:68305) has a powerful melee attack and a large amount of health.<br/><br/>(npc:68305) has two goblins on his shoulders at the start of the fight. Kill them first, which will make (npc:68305) take 100% increased damage until the fight ends. This will also make it easier to beat the 2-minute enrage timer.<br/><br/><b>Casters can stun, slow or root to keep him at a distance.<br/><b>Get behind (npc:68305) when he casts (spell:134650) and continue with DPS as fast as possible.<br/><b>Melee players need to mitigate the damage from his melee attacks.<br/><b>(npc:68305) is not a difficult boss.|	
|NPCID|68250| |NAME|Unguloxx| |LVL|Rank 6.4| |ABIL|| |ST|(npc:68250) has no abilities, he will only melee you.<br/><br/>Melee players need to use their defensive cooldowns wisely. They can't do much except try to kill (npc:68250) before he kills them.<br/><br/>Ranged players should keep (npc:68250) at a distance, as he hits hard.|	
|NPCID|71081| |NAME|Mecha-Bruce| |LVL|Rank 6 Special| |ABIL|142795,142788,142756,135340,142769| |ST|(npc:70666) is a Rank 6 special boss that requires a quest to unlock, the item (item:97983) dropped by (npc:67262) when you defeat him using his Challenge Card.<br/><br/>(npc:71081) has 6.5 M hp. Attacks like ordinary (npc:67262), except he will use an ability called (spell:142795) which he will channel for a few seconds, and afterwards he will use (spell:142769) which will stun your character for 3 seconds.<br/><br/>He will use the upgrade every other (spell:142788) phase, so he will chomp, upgrade, chomp, chomp, upgrade, chomp, chomp, upgrade, etc. Every upgrade makes him faster and stronger (spell:142756).<br/><br/>He will move faster, attack faster, and channel his abilities faster. The longer the fight goes on, the more likely you will be chomped when he stuns you due to his insane speed.<br/><br/>Keep him in the corners. When he chomps, you can DPS him for the duration, then run to the opposite end when he is using his upgrade ability. Save your big movement speed CDs for the end, as you will have less and less time after each upgrade. If you have a pet/pets with a taunt or can tank, then he will chomp your pet after he stuns you. He will not stun your pets, always the player, but will chomp the highest aggro. If you are melee, best advice is to burn him as fast as possible.|	
|NPCID|70740| |NAME|Blingtron 3000| |LVL|Rank 6 Special| |ABIL|141229,141359| |ST|(npc:70740) is a Rank 6 special boss that requires a quest to unlock, the item (item:97985) rarely contained in (item:86623) which is available from (npc:43929) daily quest (qid:31752). (npc:43929) can be summoned by (item:87214) crafted by engineering profession.<br/><br/>(npc:70740) will spawns at one corner of the arena at the start of the encounter. When he spawns, you can dps him a little, but there is little point doing so until he gets (spell:141229).<br/><br/>(npc:70740) will cast a missile every so often, and this missile targets your current location. A large red targeting circle will spawn, marking where it will land...there is quite a bit of time for you to move out of it before the missile lands, so getting hit is not hard to avoid.<br/><br/>The tricky part is chaining electricity from the (npc:70743) at the opposite end of the room to Blingtron; at 21 million health, you need him to receive the shock from the tesla, which increases his damage taken by 900% and will stun him, preventing him from doing anything except standing there and taking the punishment!<br/><br/>Every so often, a small (npc:70802) will spawn from the gold pile next to (npc:70740), and immediately run straight to you. These NPCs have about 143k health, and "killing" them causes them to be stunned at 1 hp at the spot that you "killed" them. What you need to do is chain these mobs from (npc:70740)'s corner to that of the (npc:70743) so that the shock will jump back to him.<br/><br/>The encounter involves moving your way from one corner of the room to the other, while damaging the (npc:70802) mobs and leaving them in a trail. You need to keep an eye on the missile he launches at regular intervals. Whenever possible, stand a few yards away from where you would like to drop your next link in the chain until the red target spawns under you - that way it won't interfere with you as you dps down the add in the correct location.<br/><br/>The adds need to be roughly 8-10 yards apart to trigger the jumps. Don't leave large gaps, and don't AoE...single target dps is the key to making a proper line. Also, you may need to manually target each new mob - tab targeting tends to target nearby inactive bots that you have already placed.<br/><br/>When your chain is complete, you need to click the (npc:70743) to activate it. This involves a cast bar, so be prepared for that and don't get blasted by a (spell:141359) while activating it! Once activated, you need to make a beeline for an empty corner - if you are too close to any (npc:70802) (active or stunned) such that the (npc:70743) shock bounces to you, it's game over! Give it a healthy distance, especially since more bots will continue to spawn and run towards you. The shock will bounce from add to add all the way back to (npc:70740), stunning him.<br/><br/>Finally - now you have to DPS (npc:70740) down! Save all your cooldowns for this part, because even with 900% increased damage taken, the first part of the fight will have gone on long enough that you will need every bit of burst you can muster. You will not need to avoid anything or worry about mechanics at this stage, except for avoiding the enrage timer until (npc:70740) is dead!<br/><br/>It may take a few tries to get the correct timing/placement, if you are overly cautious and make your bots spaced to closely together, you will run out of time! Don't let the sparks that crackle between the bots distract you, as long as there is about 10 yards separating the bots, the shock will jump ok. You will need roughly 7 bots, give or take a couple.|	
|NPCID|67487| |NAME|Bo Bobble| |LVL|Rank 7.1| |ABIL|133162,133172,133249| |ST|(npc:67488) and (npc:67487) have a shared health pool of 11M.<br/><br/>(npc:67488) frequently uses (spell:133212). This fires rockets at you, but seems to have poor aim, so they end up being shot around the arena. They deal lots of damage (about 250k) and will knock you back a bit. The plus side is that they can also damage (npc:67488) and (npc:67487).<br/><br/>Look for circles on the ground, as these indicate where the rockets will land. Move away if you're standing on one.<br/><br/>(npc:67487) frequently casts (spell:133172) which deals about 90k damage. There is not much you can do about this as they come one after another. Just try to mitigate the damage and self heal.<br/><br/>There are four (npc:67500), one in each corner of the arena. (npc:67487) sometimes moves to a generator, where he protects himself or anyone under it (including you) from any damage. The (npc:67500) has about 800k health and can be destroyed. So three hits from the rockets is usually enough to destroy it.<br/><br/><b>Always stand beside (npc:67487), so the rockets will hit him instead of you.<br/><b>Always avoid the rockets, by moving out of the circles on the ground.<br/><b>When a (npc:67500) is activated, always move under it. This will attract the rockets, so it is destroyed.<br/><b>Be wary of the shield bugging and actually causing you damage.<br/><b>Don't DPS (npc:67487), as he is immune.<br/><b>You can DPS (npc:67488).<br/><b>Classes without self heals are in for a tough fight.|	
