|NPCID|70659| |NAME|Hexos| |LVL|Rank 8.1| |ABIL|140849| |ST|(npc:70659) uses (spell:140849), which pulls you to the center of the arena and locks you in place for 2 minutes.<br/><br/>He has no abilities or melee attack.<br/><br/>(spell:140834) which look like purple hexagonal patterns will move towards you throughout the fight. If the (spell:140834) touches your face, then you will die.<br/><br/>(npc:70659) will always face you, so this means that as the patterns approach, you need to constantly keep turning to face the empty gap.<br/><br/>All you can do is attack him, while you keep turning to avoid the maze of purple patterns.<br/><br/>Prevent death effects such as (spell:31230) or (spell:86949) can save you.<br/><br/>You need to kill (npc:70659) before the 2 minute enrage timer.<br/><br/>Rotating can be very distracting. You only need 100k DPS to kill (npc:70659), so you can simplify your DPS rotation until you drop to 120k or 130k DPS. Depending on your gear, you will be able to drop some spells and attacks, making it easier to focus on turning your character.<br/><br/>One of the hardest NPC's in Brawler's Guild.|	
|NPCID|70733| |NAME|Tyson Sanders| |LVL|Rank 8.2| |ABIL|| |ST|(npc:70733) summons three types of chickens to attack you. He doesn't attack you himself.<br/><br/>(npc:70732) will explode with (spell:141038) dealing a high amount of damage.<br/>(npc:70731) casts (spell:141129) at you. This knocks you back and deals damage.<br/>(npc:69273) follows you around meleeing you. They deal very little damage.<br/><br/>First kill the (npc:70732)<br/><br/>Keep moving around to prevent (spell:141129) from hitting you.<br/><br/>Ignore the (npc:69273), only kill them if you have to.<br/><br/>Lastly attack (npc:70733).<br/><br/>Turning off nameplates can help you avoid getting into range of (npc:70732) by accident.|	
|NPCID|70983| |NAME|T440 Dual-Mode Robot| |LVL|Rank 8.3| |ABIL|141477,141395,141404,141396,141401| |ST|The (npc:70983) has two fighting modes: melee and ranged.<br/><br/>(npc:70983) changes mode depending on your position. If you are in melee range of (npc:70983), it is in (spell:141395) and will melee you.<br/><br/>If you are not in melee range, (npc:70983) is in (spell:141400) and will cast (spell:141474).<br/><br/>The longer the (npc:70983) stays in one mode, the faster it attacks and the more damage it does. This stacking buff gets dangerous at around 15 stacks.<br/><br/>About every 10 seconds, make it change attack mode by moving yourself closer or farther away to it (depending on what mode it is currently in). This will keep the damage manageable.<br/><br/>When the robot changes mode, it deals you with moderate damage from (spell:141404)|	
|NPCID|70977| |NAME|Anthracite| |LVL|Rank 8.4| |ABIL|141371,141403,141369,142400| |ST|(npc:70977) has two states he can be in:<br/><br/>(spell:141388) where he deals damage to you every second with (spell: 142400) and damages you every time you attack him. This is his default state and (npc:70977) will be in this state when he first spawns.<br/><br/>(spell:141371) lasts for 20 seconds and will stun (npc:70977) and make him take increased damage.<br/><br/>(spell:141371) can be triggered using (spell:141415). You can cast (spell:141415) by using the action button that appears in the middle of the screen. Face away from (npc:70977) when using (spell:141415), as it sprays water behind you, not in front of you.<br/><br/>You are only given one charge of (spell:141415). To recharge the spell, kill one of the (npc:71048) and walk through the mist that they leave behind, which grants you (spell:141496)<br/><br/>1. When (npc:70977) first spawns, face away from him and use (spell:141415).<br/><br/>2. Burn him down while he is (spell:141371).<br/><br/>3. When (spell:141371) is about to expire, kill an (npc:71048), recharge (spell:141415) and use it on (npc:70977) again.<br/><br/>4. Repeat until (npc:70977) dies.<br/><br/>Note: You do not want to be attacking (npc:70977) while he is (spell:141388)|	
|NPCID|70694| |NAME|Big Badda Boom| |LVL|Rank 9.1| |ABIL|140995,140996| |ST|(npc:70694) has only a weak melee attack. After you damage him some, he will explode and split into two smaller (npc:70694), this explosion hurts a bit more than the melee. As you damage the two new mobs, they too will explode and split into two more (npc:70694).<br/><br/>This continues several times until you end up facing a whole bunch of very tiny bombs. To meet the DPS requirement you will have to AoE, but AoEing down the bombs causes the explosions to all go off at once and thus hurt quite a bit.<br/><br/><b>Focus on destroying the larger (npc:70694) first.<br/>Save your burst and defensive cooldown when you AoE towards the win the fight. |	
|NPCID|70656| |NAME|Nibbleh| |LVL|Rank 9.2| |ABIL|140914,140865,141013| |ST|(npc:70656) is a WoW version of the classic game Snake. As he moves, he will leave a trail of poison behind him. If he crosses his own poison trail, he gains (spell:140865), increasing his damage by 500% and decreasing damage taken by half for each stack. Clearly, stacks of this are very, very bad.<br/><br/>He will also occasionally (spell:141013) of this poison in addition to the trail he leaves. This has the same exact effect and complicates the kiting action.<br/><br/>His standard melee attack and ranged (spell:140914) are not very threatening on their own. The challenge becomes dealing enough damage to (npc:70656) while kiting him such that he never stops moving, but never crosses his own poison trail. If you can survive the full 2 minutes, 112k DPS is needed to kill him -- but you can easily run out of room well before that number if your kiting isn't perfect. Good luck!|	
|NPCID|70739| |NAME|Doctor FIST| |LVL|Rank 9.3| |ABIL|141102,141104,141041,141100,141103| |ST|(npc:70739) himself has about 13M HP, requiring about 109k sustained DPS to meet enrage.<br/><br/>All of (npc:70739) abilities will hit you for around 100k damage if you're struck.<br/><br/>Four of (npc:70739) abilities are a cone effect in front of the boss. The last one, (spell:141104), is a full 360 degrees within a 20 yard radius around the boss. All the abilities are clearly marked on the ground of the area they will affect with brownish dust, so it's easy to tell if you're in the zone of being hit. The best strategy is to hug the boss and either run through him when he casts or side-step the (spell:141102),  (spell:141041), (spell:141100) or (spell:141103) and then run away from (spell:141104).<br/><br/>After (spell:141104), immediately run back to the boss and hugged him, and repeated the process.|	
|NPCID|70068| |NAME|Ahoo'ru| |LVL|Rank 9.4| |ABIL|142621,142624,138901,142581| |ST|(npc:70068) a 2 phase encounter which you have to still kill him in under 2 minutes.<br/><br/>Phase 1: He starts out by spawning and giving you ~5 seconds to put some damage into him, however, don't pop any cooldowns. He will then gain (spell:138901) that you have to break.<br/><br/><b>Lots of shiny orbs will appear around the room that move rather slow. Avoid them as best as you can as they hit for ~200k.<br/><b>One orb will be extra sparkly. You need to run over and touch this orb.<br/><b>Once you touch it, it spawns a (npc:70081). You have to damage the (npc:70081) to around half HP before it casts (spell:138845).<br/><b>You need to run to the opposite side of (npc:70068) so the (spell:138845) hits him. This knocks off one of his shield stacks.<br/><b>Do this 3 times then to move to phase 2.<br/><br/>Phase 2: The room clears and this is your DPS phase. Use every DPS cooldown you have to kill him and he will use 2 important spell in this phase.<br/><br/><b>First is (spell:142621) in which requires to be interrupted. <br/><b>Second is (spell:142583) in which he summons many orbs around you and roots you for 2 second. You must get out as soon as possible by using a root break ability and avoid as much of the orbs as you can.<br/><br/>You will need to avoid (spell:142583) a few times and beat the enrage and you will win!|	
|NPCID|70794| |NAME|Blind Hero| |LVL|Rank 9 Special| |ABIL|141192,141189,141190| |ST|(npc:70794) is a Rank 9 special boss that requires a quest to unlock, the item (item:97987) starts the quest and it is rarely found in (item:93724) a reward from Darkmoon Daily quests.<br/><br/>(npc:70794) is easy for range class but can be difficult for melee. He has three abilities: <br/><br/><b>(spell:141189) does damage 180 degree in front of him, where you (or your pet) attacked him last.<br/><b>(spell:141190) is a 45 degree cone, again targeting where he was last hit.<br/><b>(spell:141192) does 360 degree damage within ~20 yards. This can be dodged and parried.<br/><br/>He will always do this rotation (spell:141189), 4 (spell:141190) then (spell:141192). <br/><br/>1. The best way to dodge (spell:141190) is by circling behind him after he casts the first (spell:141189) in each rotation. Then, wait for him to turn and face you before you move. As soon as he faces your new spot, run about 90 degrees to either right or left (circular around him) then stop. Stay as close to him as possible while rotating to minimize the distance you need to run but DO NOT run through him; running through him makes it very difficult to predict the direction of his next (spell:141190). Wait for his swing to miss and wait for him to face you again. As soon as he faces you again, you move another 90 degrees. Repeat this for all 4 (spell:141190).<br/><br/>2. Remember how many Swift Strikes he does so you can prepare to move away from (spell:141192) after the 4th (spell:141190).|	
|NPCID|70616| |NAME|Mingus Diggs| |LVL|Rank 9 Special| |ABIL|140758,142807| |ST|(npc:70616) is a Rank 9 special boss that requires a quest to unlock, the item (item:97986) begins the quest and it is rarely found in (item:87539) Requires Archaeology (600).<br/><br/>This fight evolves around the four statues: (npc:70617), (npc:70618), (npc:70619), and (npc:70620), one standing in each corner of the Brawler's Ring. Each statue will start stacking a debuff on you:  (spell:140754), (spell:140751),  (spell:140748), and (spell:140746) that gets more and more painful and stacks really fast, about 2 stacks a second. <br/><br/>The basic idea is that if you stand next to one of them, it will deactivate and stop casting everything to wear off the debuff, thus taking less damage. (npc:70616)will also be chasing you around and hitting you with his shovel for weak melee damage. He is immune to damage through (spell:142807) till the four statues are killed.<br/><br/>Manage the stacking debuffs by running around dropping them as needed. As ranged you are able to dps the statues while deactivating another debuff; utilize this to your advantage. Melee need to manage debuffs a bit closer or risk taking added damage, ideally you need to keep bouncing between statues to minimize debuff stacks. Abilities like (spell:31224), (spell:45438), (spell:110700), (spell:122783) etc., are useful to drop the debuff stack when damage gets overwhelming. Balance and feral druids can utilize (spell:110309) to their advantage to be able to drop stacks when required.|	
|NPCID|67490| |NAME|Epicus Maximus| |LVL|Special Boss| |ABIL|133262,133250| |ST|(npc:67490) has three abilities.<br/><br/><b>The undead character riding (npc:67490) keeps throwing (spell:133205)  sonic disks on the floor.<br/><b>Epicus Maximus keeps casting (spell:133250), which creates a very slow beam of light that follows you for 12 seconds.<br/><b>Every 30 seconds, Epicus Maximus will cast (spell:133262), a very damaging spell that can be interrupted or outranged.<br/><br/>The strategy is relatively simple. Keep moving around to avoid the sonic disks and (spell:133250). Interrupt (spell:133262) (or outrange it if you are a ranged DPS).<br/><br/>Note that Epicus Maximus will sometimes not cast (spell:133250) and will instead melee you a few times for a small amount.|	
|NPCID|67483| |NAME|Disruptron Mk. 3R-Alpha| |LVL|Special Boss| |ABIL|135621| |ST|(npc:67483) has only one ability: (spell:135621). It stuns players within 8 yards.<br/><br/>Other than that, there are horizontal laser walls moving along either the south-north axis or the west-east axis. They deal damage to you when they touch you, but you can jump over them.<br/><br/>Also, there are 3 cannons around the room. Each of them sends disks flying around the room in various directions. For most of the fight, only one laser is active at a given time. At 35% health, the boss will activate them all.<br/><br/>So, the strategy for this fight is to keep jumping over the laser walls and avoid the sonic disks. Jumping over the laser walls has the highest priority. Melee players should also pay attention to (spell:135621) and interrupt it.<br/><br/>When the boss reaches 35% health, he will activate all cannons, suddenly making the fight much harder. This is a good time to use all your DPS cooldowns.|	
|NPCID|67571| |NAME|Millhouse Manastorm| |LVL|Special Boss| |ABIL|133650,133654,134772,133655,133398| |ST|(npc:67571) has three abilities: (spell:133654), (spell:133655), and (spell:134772). The first two deal a bit of damage to you, but are of no consequence on the strategy. (spell:134772) knocks you back if you get within 3 yards of (npc:67571).<br/><br/>In addition, (npc:67571) will summon 2 (npc:67612) every 15 seconds. Each (npc:67612) channels a beam of light towards (npc:67571). These beams buff him every second with (spell:133379). This buff stacks up to 100 and every stack increases damage done by 5%.<br/><br/>The strategy for this fight is simple. The idea is to keep stacking (spell:133379) on yourself while preventing (npc:67571) from stacking it on himself.<br/><br/>Whenever a new set of (npc:67612) spawn, you need to intercept one of the beams, so that (spell:133379) stacks on yourself, and you need to destroy the (npc:67612) channeling the other beam (preventing (npc:67571) from receiving any stack). If you have a pet, you can positioning on the other beam so it intercepts it (this way, you do not need to waste time destroying the (npc:67612) that channels it).<br/><br/>When a new set of (npc:67612) appear, there will be 4 beams for a few seconds. This should not distract you and you should immediately stop dealing with the old set of (npc:67612) and start dealing with the new one. It is not a problem if (npc:67571) receives a few stacks of (spell:133379) from the old set of (npc:67612). These stacks will drop before he summons a new set of (npc:67612).<br/><br/>When you reach about 80 stacks of (spell:133379), you should use all your DPS cooldowns to burn the boss.|	
|NPCID|67518| |NAME|Zen'shar| |LVL|Special Boss| |ABIL|133208,134772| |ST|(npc:67518) himself has two abilities: (spell:133208) and (spell:134772). (spell:133208) is a laser beam that follows you around for 4 seconds; (npc:67518) keeps casting it. Get Off knocks you back if you get too close to him.<br/><br/>In addition to (npc:67518)'s abilities, you will notice that shadowy void zones often appear on the ground and that there are eyes flying around the room, which summon beams of light that roam around the arena. As the fight drags on, there will be more and more of these beams of light.<br/><br/>So, to defeat (npc:67518), you need to keep moving around to avoid all the abilities we have mentioned above. Avoiding the beams of light from the flying eyes will occupy most of your time, as the other two abilities ((spell:133208)and the shadowy void zones) are very easy to deal with.<br/><br/>Note that, initially, you need to kill the (npc:67519) that circle around (npc:67518) before you can attack him. We advise you to keep your DPS cooldowns for when (npc:67518) becomes attackable and then simpy burn him down.|
